text: Inga Tavdishvili (, born July 20, 1982 in Rustavi) is a Georgian rhythmic gymnast. Tavdishvili competed for Georgia in the rhythmic gymnastics individual all-around competition at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney. There she was 21st in the qualification round and did not advance to the final. == References == == External links == * * Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:Rhythmic gymnasts from Georgia (country) Category:Gymnasts at the 2000 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic gymnasts of Georgia (country) Category:People from Rustavi
